# Brute

TC : O(N³ + V log M) (worst case O(N³ log N), commonly simplified to O(N³) in interviews and DSA discussions) 
V = number of valid triplets found
M = number of unique triplets stored

SC : O(M)
Auxiliary space (excluding the output) is also O(M) because of the set

#include <bits/stdc++.h> 
vector<vector<int>> findTriplets(vector<int>arr, int n, int K) {
	
	set<vector<int>> st;

	for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
		for(int j=i+1; j<n; j++){
			for(int k=j+1; k<n; k++){
				if(arr[i] + arr[j] + arr[k] == K){
					vector<int> temp = {arr[i], arr[j], arr[k]};
					sort(temp.begin(), temp.end());
					st.insert(temp);
				}
			}
		}
	}
	vector<vector<int>> ans(st.begin(), st.end());
	return ans;
}



